com.complexible.common.rdf.random

Class RandomValueGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.common.collect.UnmodifiableIterator<org.openrdf.model.Value>
      • com.complexible.common.rdf.random.RandomValueGenerator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterator<org.openrdf.model.Value>

    public class RandomValueGenerator
extends com.google.common.collect.UnmodifiableIterator<org.openrdf.model.Value>
    Generates an infinite sequence of random RDF terms. Configuration options can be used to control what kind of terms are generated. When next() is called the value probabilites are used to decide if a URI, bnode, or a literal will be generated. The literal probabilities are used to decide what kind of literal is generated. Only plain, integer, float, double, or dateTime literals will be generated. Setting any probability top 0 will disable generation of that type.
    Since:
    0.9.6
    Version:
    3.1.2
    Author:
    Evren Sirin
